{
  "texts": [
    "Robustness is a key factor influencing trust in AI.",
    "Rempel et al. (1985) identified three components of trust from a dynamic perspective, including predictability (the consistency of actions over time), dependability (reliability based on past experience), and faith (belief in future behavior).",
    "Based on the definitions, these components also correspond to the formation of the perception of robustness.",
    "Compared to trust in humans, building trust in AI takes more time; moreover, when AI encounters problems, the loss of trust in it happens more rapidly (Dzindolet et al., 2003).",
    "Furthermore, the simpler the task in which the error occurs, the greater the loss of trust (Madhavan et al., 2006)."
  ]
}